Subject: Fix StringPiece API compatibility for modern C++ string_view
Upstream: No
Origin: Wolfi OS (GCC 15 / Modern C++ compatibility fix)
Author: Wolfi OS Maintainers

The legacy RE2 StringPiece implementation had an .as_string() method that
has been removed in modern C++ where StringPiece is aliased to std::string_view.
Replace .as_string() with std::string() constructor for conversion.

--- a/src/3rdparty/chromium/gpu/command_buffer/service/program_manager.cc
+++ b/src/3rdparty/chromium/gpu/command_buffer/service/program_manager.cc
@@ -620,7 +620,7 @@
       output += hashed_name;
   }

-  return output + input.as_string();
+  return output + std::string(input);
 }

